<!--
  PROFILE CUSTOM CONTENT SNIPPET

  Adds SOUL content to the character profile page.

  FILE: ares-webportal/app/components/profile-custom.hbs

  INSTALLATION:

  1. Open your game's ares-webportal/app/components/profile-custom.hbs.
  2. Copy the code block below this comment:
     - If the file is empty or nearly empty, paste it as-is.
     - If it already has other tab panes, add this after another pane's
       closing </div>.

  ID MATCHING:
  - id="soul-tab-pane" must match the href in
    profile-custom-tabs.snippet.hbs.

  PROPERTY NAMES:
  - These examples use "char", matching the standard profile component.
  - If your profile uses "character" instead, update every "this.char".
  - If the target file is empty, check the template that invokes
    <ProfileCustom>. The argument passed there is the property available
    here.

  REQUIRED BACKEND SETUP:
  - Install custom-install/custom_char_fields.snippet.rb first.
  - Approval status and viewer identity are not part of the base profile
    payload. They must be read from this.char.custom, as shown below.
  - There is no separate this.viewer object in this component.

  SHARED FIELD NAMES:
  - This snippet uses the shared is_approved and viewer_id keys from the
    custom-fields snippet.
  - If another plugin already supplies equivalent keys under different
    names, reuse those keys and update both profile snippets accordingly.

  AUTHORIZATION:
  - The visibility check below keeps the tab out of the interface when
    SOUL is disabled or the character is neither approved nor being viewed
    by SOUL staff.
  - Each SOUL web operation performs its own server-side authorization.
    These client-side checks are presentation only.
  - XP is self-service. The isSelf argument prevents the XP component from
    loading or displaying the viewer's XP on somebody else's profile.

  WEB PORTAL OPTIONAL:
  - This integration is optional. SOUL remains usable through MUSH commands
    without these snippets.
-->

{{#if (and this.char.custom.soul_enabled (or this.char.custom.is_approved this.char.custom.can_manage_soul))}}
  <div class="tab-pane fade" id="soul-tab-pane">
    {{soul/sheet character=this.char.name}}
    {{soul/xp character=this.char.name isSelf=(eq this.char.id this.char.custom.viewer_id)}}
    {{soul/bnb}}
    {{soul/culmination character=this.char.name}}
    {{soul/history character=this.char.name}}
    {{#if this.char.custom.can_manage_soul}}
      {{soul/staff}}
    {{/if}}
  </div>
{{/if}}
